---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<Base title="What's Next for Stratum — Listening, Hardening, Shipping | Stratum Blog" description="Stratum v0.2.3 is out. Here's where we're headed: community feedback, security hardening, and a developer-first roadmap.">

<!-- Nav -->
<nav class="nav">
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="/" class="nav-logo">
      <img src="/favicon.png" alt="Stratum" class="nav-logo-img" width="28" height="28" />
      Stratum
    </a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/what-is-stratum">What is Stratum?</a>
      <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
      <a href="https://docs.stratum-hq.org">Docs</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum">GitHub</a>
      <button class="theme-toggle" id="theme-toggle" aria-label="Toggle theme">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5"/>
          <line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="3"/>
          <line x1="12" y1="21" x2="12" y2="23"/>
          <line x1="4.22" y1="4.22" x2="5.64" y2="5.64"/>
          <line x1="18.36" y1="18.36" x2="19.78" y2="19.78"/>
          <line x1="1" y1="12" x2="3" y2="12"/>
          <line x1="21" y1="12" x2="23" y2="12"/>
          <line x1="4.22" y1="19.78" x2="5.64" y2="18.36"/>
          <line x1="18.36" y1="5.64" x2="19.78" y2="4.22"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- Article -->
<article class="post">
  <header class="post-header">
    <p class="post-eyebrow">Blog</p>
    <h1>What's Next for <span class="accent">Stratum</span></h1>
    <p class="post-intro">We shipped the foundation. Now we're listening.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="post-body">

    <h2>v0.2.3 is out. Now what?</h2>
    <p>
      Stratum v0.2.3 landed with tree-structured tenants, config inheritance, three isolation
      strategies, GDPR tooling, a hierarchical ABAC policy engine, and a NestJS integration
      package. That's a lot of surface area for a young library. We're proud of what's there,
      but we're also clear-eyed about what comes next.
    </p>
    <p>
      The honest answer: we're waiting. Not passively, but deliberately. The most important
      thing we can do right now is hear from developers who actually try Stratum in their
      own codebases, with their own schemas, against their own edge cases.
    </p>

    <h2>We need your issues and feature requests</h2>
    <p>
      If you're evaluating Stratum for a project, we want to know what you run into. Does
      the config inheritance model fit your use case? Is the tenant tree depth sufficient?
      Did schema isolation behave the way you expected? What's missing from the API that
      would make adoption easier?
    </p>
    <p>
      These aren't rhetorical questions. We built Stratum based on patterns we've seen
      across dozens of B2B SaaS codebases, but no library survives first contact with the
      real world unchanged. The gap between what we designed and what you need is where the
      best improvements will come from.
    </p>
    <p>
      Open an issue on <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum/issues" class="post-link">GitHub</a>.
      Tell us what broke. Tell us what's awkward. Tell us what you wished existed. Every
      issue filed makes Stratum better for the next team that picks it up.
    </p>

    <h2>Security-first, not security-later</h2>
    <p>
      Multi-tenancy libraries sit at the foundation of your data layer. A bug in tenant
      isolation isn't a UI glitch. It's a data breach. We take that responsibility seriously.
    </p>
    <p>
      Stratum's Row-Level Security policies are generated, not hand-written. Schema isolation
      creates real PostgreSQL schemas with enforced boundaries. The ABAC policy engine
      evaluates attribute-based rules at the library level before queries reach the database.
      These aren't shortcuts. They're deliberate design choices that put correctness ahead of
      convenience.
    </p>
    <p>
      Going forward, security hardening is the top priority. We're investing in:
    </p>
    <ul class="post-list">
      <li>Comprehensive test coverage for isolation boundary edge cases</li>
      <li>Fuzz testing tenant resolution and config inheritance paths</li>
      <li>Third-party security review before we call anything 1.0</li>
      <li>Clear documentation of the threat model and what Stratum does (and does not) protect against</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If you find a security issue, please report it responsibly. We'll treat every report
      with urgency.
    </p>

    <h2>Developer experience is the product</h2>
    <p>
      A library that's correct but painful to use doesn't get adopted. We're committed to
      making Stratum something you actually enjoy wiring into your stack.
    </p>
    <p>
      That means better TypeScript types so your editor catches mistakes before your tests do.
      It means clear, honest error messages that point you toward the fix, not just the failure.
      It means documentation that respects your time: quick starts that actually work in under
      five minutes, API references that don't hide the important parts behind three clicks.
    </p>
    <p>
      We're also working on framework adapters. The NestJS package shipped in v0.2.3. Express
      and Fastify adapters are in progress. The goal is the same everywhere: wire in your pool,
      call <code>initialize()</code>, and get back to building your product.
    </p>

    <h2>What we're not doing</h2>
    <p>
      We're not rushing to 1.0 to put a number on the README. We're not adding features
      nobody asked for. We're not building a SaaS dashboard or a hosted offering before the
      core library is rock-solid.
    </p>
    <p>
      The roadmap is simple: listen to developers, harden what exists, and ship what's
      actually needed. No vanity features. No premature abstractions. Just a multi-tenancy
      library that works and keeps working.
    </p>

    <h2>Get involved</h2>
    <p>
      Stratum is MIT licensed and built in the open. The best way to shape its future is to
      use it and tell us what happens.
    </p>
    <ul class="post-list">
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum/issues" class="post-link">Open an issue</a>
        with bugs, feature requests, or questions
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum/discussions" class="post-link">Start a discussion</a>
        if you want to talk through a use case before filing
      </li>
      <li>
        Star the <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum" class="post-link">repo</a>
        so we know you're watching
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We built Stratum because the Node.js ecosystem needed it. Where it goes from here
      depends on the developers who use it.
    </p>

  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="post-cta">
    <div class="post-cta-install">
      <code>npm install @stratum-hq/lib pg</code>
    </div>
    <div class="post-cta-links">
      <a href="https://docs.stratum-hq.org/getting-started/quick-start" class="btn-primary">Read the docs</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum" class="btn-secondary">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

<!-- Footer -->
<footer class="footer">
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <p class="footer-meta">
      MIT License &middot; &copy; <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq">Stratum HQ</a>
    </p>
    <div class="footer-links">
      <a href="https://docs.stratum-hq.org">Docs</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum">GitHub</a>
      <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/org/stratum-hq">npm</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>

<style>
  .post {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: calc(var(--space-8) * 4) var(--space-6) var(--space-8);
  }

  .post-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .post-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--sandstone);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .post-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .post-intro {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .post-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .post-body p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .post-body strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .post-body code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875em;
    color: var(--sandstone);
    background: var(--code-bg);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .post-link {
    color: var(--sandstone);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .post-link:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .post-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4) 0;
  }

  .post-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .post-list li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.7em;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--sandstone);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .post-cta {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .post-cta-install {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--code-text);
  }

  .post-cta-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .post {
      padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-4);
    }
  }
</style>

<!-- Theme toggle -->
<script>
  const toggle = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');
  const html = document.documentElement;

  function setTheme(theme: string) {
    html.setAttribute('data-theme', theme);
    localStorage.setItem('theme', theme);
  }

  const saved = localStorage.getItem('theme');
  if (saved) setTheme(saved);

  toggle?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const current = html.getAttribute('data-theme');
    setTheme(current === 'light' ? 'dark' : 'light');
  });
</script>

</Base>
